wikipedia_page.main: Eustace Malden (19 August 1863 – 3 December 1947) was an English cricketer. He played thirteen first-class matches for Kent between 1892 and 1893.

response: Malden was born in Sheldwich in Kent in 1870. His only first-class appearance was against MCC in June 1893 at Lord's.Ernest Malden, CricketArchive. Retrieved 2018-09-30.  His cousin Eustace Malden, played 12 times for Kent between 1892 and 1893Eustace Malden, CricketArchive. Retrieved 2018-09-30.  and Eustace's son, Jack Malden, also played 24 first-class matches, mainly for Sussex in the early 1920s.Jack Malden, CricketArchive. Retrieved 2018-09-30.

Malden died at Kingston Warren near Newbury in Berkshire in November 1963 aged 64.William Malden, CricInfo. Retrieved 30 September 2018. His father Eustace Malden also played first-class cricket as did his father's cousin Ernest Malden.
